column1: PCPB-961 - Service Chaining external SF- PCG
column29:
PCG is a new cloud native architecture (containers) vs EPG based on VMs. 

Target of the feature is that new PCG can communicate with external SF as they are supported in legacy EPG to facilitate seamless customer migration from EPG3 to PCG.

SFD: [LEGACY | https://erilink.ericsson.se/eridoc/erl/objectId/09004cffc278039e?docno=1/0360-1/FCP111486Uen&action=current&format=ppt12]

column1: US1: SF DONE SUPPORT IN SC ENGINE
column29:
Implement the callback for a eSF to be able to perform SF DONE action at flow level

If an eSF performs SF DONE, the engine will stop sending traffic to such eSF for this flow.

This is expected to improve the performance of scenarios where 1 eSF is active and only have to process a percentage of the traffic, since such eSF won’t be called for the flows is not “interested in”. (once US3 is implemented)
